===Asia-Pacific Group===
The [[Asia]]-[[Oceania|Pacific]] Group (formerly the Asian Group) has 53 members (27.5% of all UN members) and is the second largest regional group by number of member states (one fewer than the African Group). Its territory is composed of much of the continents of [[Asia]] and [[Oceania]]. However, [[Russia]] and the [[Caucasus|Caucasian]] states are members of the [[Eastern European Group]] and [[Australia]], [[New Zealand]], [[Israel]], and [[Turkey]] are all members of the Western European and Others Group. The Asia-Pacific Group has three seats on the [[Security Council]]: China's permanent seat, and two non-permanent seats. The Group also has 11 seats on the United Nations Economic and Social Council and 13 seats on the United Nations Human Rights Council. In the rotation of the post of the President of the United Nations General Assembly, the group is eligible for having its nationals elected to this post in years ending with 1 and 6; most recently, [[Peter Thomson (diplomat)|Peter Thomson]] of [[Fiji]] was elected to this position in 2016.

